                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Balt.</placeName>
                                        <date>Aug 24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1848</date>
                              </p>
                              <p> Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Your esteemed fav. Of <date>20th</date><lb/>
                                        <add>?</add> have sooner elicited a letter to <persName>Mr
                                                  Hart</persName><lb/> (one accompanies this) has
                                        the proximity<add>?</add><lb/> both from the uncertainty in
                                        which you stood as<lb/> to the more commanding claims of
                                        your own Congr,<lb/> and our own as the day had not been
                                                  <add>?</add><lb/> fixed until <persName>Mr
                                                  Jonas</persName> return. I have not been<lb/> able
                                        to name any definite day until now.</p>
                              <p>We had been desirous to select the second <add>?</add><lb/> for
                                        several reasons of greater convenience but<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr J</persName> wishes to be in <placeName>N.
                                                  O.</placeName> by the <date>2nd<add>?</add>
                                                  Oct.</date> when<lb/> his business requires his
                                        presence, &amp; he has<lb/> promised to give a week to his
                                        friend in <placeName>Cini.</placeName><lb/> so we have been
                                                  over<add>?</add>. the <sic>rether</sic> as he
                                        informs<lb/> us you prefer the first wednesday as more<lb/>
                                        convenient to your self and <persName>Conn.</persName> you
                                        will<lb/> we hope take the occasion to spend a few days<lb/>
                                        with us, we will provide you quarters either<lb/> with
                                                  <persName>E. P. Cohen</persName> or <persName>Mr
                                                  Bordley's</persName>, as the former<lb/> has
                                        removed to a larger house,, I have no doubt<lb/> he
                                                  <add>?</add> will be happy to house you with
                                        them<lb/> let us know however if you object to either</p>
                              <p>A marriage before night will be productive of<lb/> a great deal of
                                        inconvenience to us as we are<lb/> situated &amp; we have
                                        consulted <persName>Mr Rice</persName> who</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p><sic>who</sic> tells us that the <add>?</add> in our<lb/> laws or
                                        customs requires the ceremony at<lb/> any particular period
                                        of the day but that it<lb/> may be performed at any time
                                        &amp; that the<lb/> usage varies in different countries.</p>
                              <p>We have a precedent moreover in our own<lb/> Congr. <persName>Mrs.
                                                  E. P. Cohen</persName> tells us she was
                                        married<lb/> at 8 o'clock in the evening.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Please present our<lb/> warmest congratulations to
                                        our friend <persName>Carvalho</persName><lb/> we have not
                                        the satisfaction of knowing the<lb/> lady even by report,
                                        but hope &amp; doubt not<lb/> she is one every way qualified
                                        to promote<lb/> his happiness. bid him recollect his<lb/>
                                        promise to come to <persName>Rosalies</persName> wedding
                                        &amp; tell<lb/> him the day. We shall however enclose<lb/>
                                        him an invitation; Tell him he is designated<lb/> as
                                        groomsman, let the <persName>Sticks</persName><add>?</add>
                                        come by<lb/> all means.</p>
                              <p>Our love to <persName>Mrs Rehine</persName> and<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr Seixas</persName> &amp; when you write</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">Truly yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">
                                        <persName role="author">E. Block.</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">Please let us know at<lb/> once if the day
                                        suits.<lb/> your convenience<lb/> as we wish the
                                        invitations<lb/> to conform <add>?</add></p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>To</p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>No 118 North 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                                                  St</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
